Package: syncR
Title: Integrate and Coordinate Data Across the Circadia Lab Package Ecosystem
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Lucas", "França", , "lucas.franca@northumbria.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-HERE"))
Description: syncR is the integrator and coordinator of the Circadia Lab R ecosystem.
    It pulls sociodemographic and questionnaire data from tallieR, sleep diary data
    from slumbR, and actigraphy-derived circadian metrics from zeitR into a single
    unified, participant-indexed database. syncR::sync() — pulling everything into
    alignment, just like the SCN does.
